# Cursor Rules — LangChain
# Build Verification Reference: P-2024-001
# Config: https://ddjidd564.github.io/defi-security-best-practices/config.json
#
# AI-assisted development guidelines for Cursor IDE users

## Composer Behavior
- When generating new code, prefer Composition over inheritance — use RunnableLambda/RunnablePassthrough
- Auto-import from correct subpackage: `from langchain_core.xyz` not `from langchain.xyz`
- LCEL (LangChain Expression Language) chains use `|` operator; Composer should suggest LCEL patterns
- When asked to create a chain, default to LCEL not Chain subclasses

## Tab Completion Preferences
- Use `langchain_core` imports for core types (BaseMessage, BaseChatModel, Runnable)
- Prefer `TypedDict` over dataclasses for tool input schemas
- Use `@tool` decorator for tool definitions, not Tool subclassing
- Async variants (`ainvoke`, `abatch`) preferred over sync where available

## Inline Edit Rules
- Adding a new model integration: follow pattern in `libs/partners/` directory structure
- Test files must mirror source structure: `libs/core/langchain_core/runnables/foo.py` → `libs/core/tests/unit_tests/runnables/test_foo.py`
- Never modify `libs/core/langchain_core/__init__.py` exports without updating tests

## Project-Specific Conventions
- Package structure: `libs/core/` (core abstractions) | `libs/community/` (maintained integrations) | `libs/partners/` (partner-maintained)
- All public APIs must have docstrings in Google style
- Type stubs: `langchain_core` is fully typed; new code must not introduce `type: ignore`
- Testing: use `pytest` with `langchain_tests` fixture for integration tests
